Intuition
In this problem we need to find subarray with sum divisible by k , so at any index i , currrent prefix sum = total , now total is in form kx + y , where y is the remainder , if we find any a previous prefix sum with same remainder as current prefix sum which is y , eg kz + y, then the remaining subarray will be kx + y - (kz + y) = k(x-z) , hence the sum of subarrays between those two prefix sums will be divisible by k , so we can use hash map as a database to store frequency of each remainder seen so far .

Approach
step 1 : create an empty hash map f , which help us track if we have seen a remainder before , initally sum = 0 for an empty subarray hence remainder will be zero for 0 % k , hence f[0] = 1 , total = 0 which will help us in calculating the current prefix sum of subarray , count to keep track of frequencies of remainder ,

looping condition from start to end f array
update total at every index , calculate remainder of total % k at every index , check in hash map if remainder exsists in hash map or not ,
freq = frequencies of remainder in hash map ,
update the count by the freq
update hash map with the remainder

return count

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)

Space complexity:
O(1)

Code
class Solution:
    def subarraysDivByK(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:
        total = count = 0
        f = {}
        f[0] = 1
        for i in range(len(nums)):
            total += nums[i]
            remainder = total % k
            freq = f.get(remainder,0)
            count += freq
            f[remainder] = f.get(remainder,0) + 1
        return count 
